article.description: UC Santa Barbara 85, Cal State-Los Angeles 57
article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 85, Cal State-Los Angeles 57
article.linkText: UC Santa Barbara 85, Cal State-Los Angeles 57
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- Orlando Johnson was a perfect 8-for-8 shooting, scoring 19 points, as UC Santa Barbara beat Cal State-Los Angeles 85-57 Saturday night. Johnson was 7-for-7 from the field and 1-for-1 from 3-point range. The only shots he missed on the night were from the free through line (4-for8). Johnson wasn't the only hot shooter for the Broncos as James Powell and Sam Phippen each put up 14 points. The Bronco's shot 53.7 percent from the field. Cal St- Los Angeles was led by guard Dwayne Jones' 15 point performance. Nuno Furtado grabbed 11 of the 33 rebounds for Cal-St-Los Angeles.
